Utility
-------

Overview:
This module contains some useful utility functions.

Files: CMakeUtilityFunctions.cmake

  Commands:

    Core_Utility_GetRepoName(url repo_name)

    Take a url ended with .git and returns the repository
    name in repo_name using a regex.

    Example:

      include(Utility)
      set(url "https://github.com/x/y.git")
      Core_Utility_GetRepoName(url repo_name)
      message(STATUS ${repo_name}) # y

